										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.etsy.com/shop/TwistyGoods" target="_blank"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2593" src="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Dandy-G-2-mini.jpg" alt="Dandy G 2 mini" width="550" height="407" srcset="http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Dandy-G-2-mini.jpg 550w, http://clockworktwist.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Dandy-G-2-mini-300x221.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /></a>Check it out!  I&#8217;m on Etsy now.  I just made a handful of bookmarks that look like cute little pocket watches.  There&#8217;s only a few designs so far, but there are more to come.  Go take a look at them in my shiny new Esty store.</p>
<p><center><script src="https://www.etsy.com/assets/js/etsy_mini_shop.js" type="text/javascript"></script><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[
new Etsy.Mini(10184139,'gallery',2,2,0,'https://www.etsy.com');
// ]]&gt;</script></center>Best of all, one of them sold before I could even list it!  I was taking photos outside in the light, when one of my neighbors asked what I was up to.  When I showed her my bookmarks, she bought one right then and there as a present for her mother.  Now there are only four of the initial batch left.  If you want one of these, you&#8217;d better get it quick!</p>
<p>Not to worry, though.  If these continue to sell well, I&#8217;ll just have to keep making more.  I&#8217;m also happy to do any sort of custom orders as well.  At the moment, my metal supplies are only of the same brass color, but I hope to branch out and try out some other antiqued metal colors as well.  Let me know in a comment if you have any suggestions.</p>
<p>And, of course, my very next design will be a replica of Twist&#8217;s watch from the books&#8230;  Keep an eye on this blog and my new store to see it as soon as I get it all put together!</p>
